  "time_ut": 1662374855,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca - \u0da9\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dbb\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Another opportunity for foreign workers - discounts on buying houses in dollars",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is decided to give a 10% discount to those who buy houses with dollars in middle income housing projects built by the Urban Development Authority. Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga, the Minister of Urban Development and Housing, says that the necessary facilities have been provided for Sri Lankans and workers abroad to buy these houses with dollars. He also mentions that this new system was introduced as a solution to the dollar crisis in the country.",
        "Two middle income housing projects implemented by the Urban Development Authority have been completed so far. The completed Borella Oval View housing project consists of 608 housing units, while the Angoda Lake Rest project consists of 500 housing units.",
        "Currently, 12 more middle income housing projects are under construction. The housing requirement met by it is 3,667 housing units. The Management Board of the Urban Development Authority has approved to facilitate the purchase of these houses by Sri Lankans and workers abroad. Minister Prasanna Ranatunga further states that priority has been given to foreign workers who have remitted foreign money through banks in a formal manner in getting these houses with dollars.",
        "The minister also states that although the new middle income projects planned by the Urban Development Authority have been temporarily stopped in the current economic situation, they have been instructed to restart them as soon as possible. Alternative measures are being taken to continue the implementation of low-facility settlement projects in Colombo city and suburbs. The minister says that these projects will be implemented without burdening the treasury.",
        "Construction of 4,074 apartment units continues with the loan support of the Asian Infrastructure and Investment Bank. The minister said that the housing projects that were planned to be implemented for families living in low-income settlements by utilizing the amount of 552 million yuan to be received as a grant from China are also expected to continue. He also claims that under this, 05 projects with 2000 housing units are to be implemented in Peliyagoda, Moratuwa, Dematagoda, Maharagama and Kottawa."
      ],
